# SOP 1.4.1 – Patrolling Areas

**Section 1 – Patrol Operations**

## Scope

To describe how patrolling areas are defined and operated across Life Saving Victoria services, including the relationships between active patrol coverage, response capability, neighbouring service awareness, and priority service delivery zones. These definitions underpin the operational use of the patrol mapping framework in LIMSOC.

This SOP defines the zones only. Operations within and outside these zones, safety obligations, and the application of these zones in LIMSOC are addressed in separate SOPs.

